Interface ServiceClient<Stub extends com.google.api.gax.core.BackgroundResource>

    public interface ServiceClient<Stub extends com.google.api.gax.core.BackgroundResource>
extends java.io.Closeable, java.lang.AutoCloseable
    Describes the API surface of an object which manages interaction with a specific Cookies API, via an underlying generated GAPIC and gRPC client set.

      • service

        @Nonnull
Stub service()
        Retrieve the stub in use by this service client, which describes the implemented API interface in raw form.

        Stubs are generated code, and so it is not advised that developers use stubs directly. As generated APIs change, there are no compatibility guarantees provided at the stub level.

        Returns:
        Stub instance implementing this service client.

      • getServiceName

        @Nonnull
java.lang.String getServiceName()
        Retrieve the short "name" for a service, which is generally a handful of characters long and represents the API service uniquely with a one-word label.

        API service names are used in routing, and generally identify services from one another.

        Returns:
        Assigned name of a given service.

      • getServiceVersion

        @Nonnull
java.lang.String getServiceVersion()
        Retrieve the version token for a service, which is generally a handful of characters long and represents the current major and minor API interface revision implemented by this client.

        API service versions indicate breaking API changes.

        Returns:
        Assigned version of a given service.
